						<summary>

						<p>This is not dated. It records that <hi rend="bold">Sadāśivadēva-Mahārāya</hi> made a gift of the village <hi rend="bold">Voḷalagundi-Bhairāpura,</hi> surnamed <hi rend="bold">Gōpināthapura,</hi> for the service of the gods Bandēśvaradēva and Gōpināthadēva in the <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> <hi rend="bold">Timmalāpura,</hi> set up by <hi rend="bold">Bayikāṟa-Rāmapaya</hi> in the temples which the latter had caused to be constructed. A copper-plate charter recording this gift is also stated to have been granted.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
